What is Stem Cell Biomanufacturing?
Stem cell biomanufacturing refers to the scalable, GMP‑compliant production of therapeutic cells such as mesenchymal stem cells, induced pluripotent stem cells, and hematopoietic stem cells. It involves meticulous control over the cell culture environment, from seed cell selection through final product formulation, to meet stringent regulatory criteria and ensure consistent potency, purity, and safety for clinical use.

